6. Conveying Non-Source Forms.

You may convey a covered work in object code form under the terms
of sections 4 and 5, provided that you also convey the
machine-readable Corresponding Source under the terms of this License,
in one of these ways:

a) Convey the object code in, or embodied in, a physical product
(including a physical distribution medium), accompanied by the
Corresponding Source fixed on a durable physical medium
customarily used for software interchange.

b) Convey the object code in, or embodied in, a physical product
(including a physical distribution medium), accompanied by a
written offer, valid for at least three years and valid for as
long as you offer spare parts or customer support for that product
model, to give anyone who possesses the object code either (1) a
copy of the Corresponding Source for all the software in the
product that is covered by this License, on a durable physical
medium customarily used for software interchange, for a price no
more than your reasonable cost of performing this source
distribution, or (2) access to copy the
Corresponding Source from a network server at no charge.

c) Convey individual copies of the object code with a copy of the
written offer to provide the Corresponding Source.  This
alternative is allowed only occasionally and noncommercially, and
only if you received the object code with such an offer, in accord
with subsection 6b.

d) If you distribute the object code by offering access from a
designated place (gratis or for a charge), offer equivalent access
to copy the Corresponding Source from the same place at no further
charge.  You need not require recipients to copy along with object
code.  If the place to copy object code is a network server, the
Corresponding Source may be on a different server (that is operated
by a third party) providing equivalent access, but you must direct
users to it clearly with prominent notices, and maintain such access
for as long as you maintain access to the object code.

e) Verify that the user already has a copy of the Corresponding
Source for this code, or that you have already sent this copy to this
user in a single transaction or batch.

For an executable work, the "Corresponding Source" need not include
unchanged modules contained in, or merely link with, the executable
work unless that executable module is, by itself, an executable work.
When you distribute the same executable with different libraries dynamically
linked with it, the work must still satisfy this requirement, as long as the
executable and its Corresponding Source are on the same medium. However,
this requirement does not apply if the executable links with the
shared libraries only in the ways that are already permitted under
this License.

